              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/SFTM_March-2021_EverydayAccountsBlog.com_2.png",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(1) During the weekend of Mimi's funeral, my uncle made cotton candy at his house. It was Carson's first time to have it, and he was such a happy boy!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(2) For the first time, Carson sat with us at church. There wasn't room at the church nursery. He was such a good boy - he sat through and watched the music, and he enjoyed playing quietly with the kids' activity pack during the sermon."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(3) Caden is still loving bathtime. Here he is looking like a Dr. Seuss character!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(4) On our first day of our trip to Port Aransas, we took our golf cart down to the beach and broke in our new sand toys. It was a fun start to our trip!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/SFTM_March-2021_EverydayAccountsBlog.com_3-1.png",
